## Bug Description

The @typespec/http-server-js emitter is not rendering parameter documentation in the generated TypeScript JSDoc comments for operation signatures.

## Expected Behavior

When TypeSpec operations have `@doc` decorators on their parameters, the generated TypeScript interface should include `@param` JSDoc tags with the parameter descriptions.

## Actual Behavior

The generated interface in `src/generated/models/all/index.ts` shows:

```typescript
export interface TestService<Context = unknown> {
  /**
   * Get a user by ID
   */
  getUser(ctx: Context, userId: string): Promise<User>;

  /**
   * Create a new user
   */
  createUser(ctx: Context, user: User): Promise<User>;
}
```

The JSDoc comments are missing the parameter documentation. It should look like:

```typescript
export interface TestService<Context = unknown> {
  /**
   * Get a user by ID
   * @param userId The ID of the user to retrieve
   */
  getUser(ctx: Context, userId: string): Promise<User>;

  /**
   * Create a new user
   * @param user The user data to create
   */
  createUser(ctx: Context, user: User): Promise<User>;
}
```

## Bug Confirmed

The bug is still present in the latest compiler version (v1.9.0). The parameter documentation from TypeSpec `@doc` decorators is not being extracted and rendered in the generated JSDoc.

